      • materializedSort

        public static <O> Iterator<O> materializedSort​(Iterator<O> unsortedIterator,
                                               Comparator<O> comparator)
        Sorts the results returned by the given iterator, returning the sorted results as a new iterator, by performing an insertion-sort into an intermediate set in memory.

        Time complexity for building an insertion sorted set is O(merge_cost * log(merge_cost)), and then iterating it makes this O(merge_cost^2 * log(merge_cost)). (Merge cost is an approximation of the cost of iterating all elements in any result set.)

        Type Parameters:
        O - The type of the objects to be sorted
        Parameters:
        unsortedIterator - An iterator which provides unsorted objects
        comparator - The comparator to use for sorting
        Returns:
        An iterator which returns the objects in sorted order
